40 grams Mature Cheddar Cheese
150 grams Basmati Rice
240 grams British Beef Mince
2 sachet(s) Peri Peri Seasoning
1 carton(s) Tomato Passata
1 carton(s) Mixed Beans
1 sachet(s) Smoky Base Paste
20 grams Butter
50 milliliter(s) Water
1 tsp Sugar

Boil a half-full kettle.
Grate the cheese.
Once boiled, pour the water into a saucepan with 1/4 tsp salt on high heat. Boil the rice, 10-12 mins.
Once cooked, drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, heat a frying pan (no oil) on medium-high heat.
Once hot, fry the beef mince, 5-6 mins. Break up the mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with salt and pepper. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.
While the beef cooks, open the remaining sachets.

Add the peri peri seasoning, passata, beans, sugar and water (see pantry for both) to the beef. Cook, 4-5 mins.
Remove from the heat and stir through the smoky base paste and butter (see pantry).
Taste and season with salt and pepper. Add a splash of water if it's a too thick.

Share rice between serving bowls.
Top with the smoky peri peri beef and sprinkle over the cheese.
Enjoy!